This paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically in the area of video segmentation. The use of super-pixels and graph-based approaches are mentioned, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as object recognition and image segmentation, falling under the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also proposes an efficient approach for video segmentation, which involves temporal consistency and real-time applications, indicating relevance to the cs.MM sub-category. The use of a graph-based approach also suggests relevance to the cs.LG sub-category, which deals with machine learning and graph-based algorithms. Additionally, the paper proposes an extension to the Felzenszwalb and Huttenlocher algorithm, indicating relevance to the cs.AI sub-category, which deals with artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper deals with the segmentation of video frames, which falls under the cs.GR sub-category, which deals with computer graphics and image processing.
